bsdsum
======

see git log for more details.

2023/01 - v1.5
* add BLAKE, BLAKE2B, BLAKE2S, BLAKE3, WHIRLPOOL algorithms
* add "mix32" (5-bit) encoding 
* add "-r" option for recursive directory access
* add "-k" option for skipping links
* add "-v" option for message reporting settings
* fix "-l" (length) and "-f" (offset) options
* add large files support on Linux (32-bit or 64-bit)
* add block devices support (only available if large files
  support is enabled)
* code reorganization
* many fixes

2022/12, 2023/01 - v1.4
* add split digest
* add binary style
* add configure script
* rewrite filelist parser
* add gcc or clang support
* add tests
* fix BSD support

2022/12/18 - v1.3
* use mmap to access content of files
* add -f (offset) and -l (length) options

2022/12/17 - v1.2
* add SHA3-256 and SHA3-512 support
* add again auto-test option [-t]
* add -s STYLE option
* change -h to help and old -h to -o
* change various options and flags

2022/12/11 - v1.1
* add libcrypto files from libressl
* add -g option (GNU output format)
* remove some options

